{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1770131420,"nonce":"rcHX/icuH7JXTrbdGGtWJ+DqvZM=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87n93Fz","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/142","origin":"github"},"title":"Auto-symlink layers/ directory to workspace worktrees","message":"## Problem\n\nWorkspace worktrees (`.workspace-worktrees/*`) don't have access to the `layers/` directory, making them incomplete for development and testing.\n\n## Current Behavior\n\nWhen creating a workspace worktree:\n```bash\ngit worktree add .workspace-worktrees/issue-138 -b feature/issue-138\ncd .workspace-worktrees/issue-138\nls layers/  # Error: No such file or directory\n```\n\n**Impact**:\n- Can't test scripts that depend on workspace structure (e.g., `make sync`)\n- Can't run builds or tests\n- Worktrees are only useful for documentation changes\n- Need manual symlink workaround: `ln -s ../../layers layers`\n\n## Root Cause\n\nThe `layers/` directory is gitignored (contains build artifacts), so it doesn't exist in git worktrees. Only the root repository files are checked out.\n\n## Comparison with Layer Worktrees\n\n**Layer worktrees** (created via `.agent/scripts/worktree_create.sh`) already handle this correctly:\n- Located in `layers/worktrees/issue-N/`\n- Automatically symlink other layers from `layers/main/`\n- Fully functional for development\n\n**Workspace worktrees** (manual git worktree creation):\n- Located in `.workspace-worktrees/issue-N/`\n- Missing `layers/` directory entirely\n- Incomplete for most development tasks\n\n## Proposed Solution\n\n### Option 1: Auto-detect and symlink (Recommended)\n\nUpdate git post-checkout hook to automatically symlink `layers/` when a worktree is detected:\n\n**Create**: `.agent/hooks/post-checkout`\n```bash\n#!/bin/bash\n# Auto-symlink layers/ in workspace worktrees\n\n# Detect if we're in a workspace worktree\nif [[ \"$PWD\" == *\"/.workspace-worktrees/\"* ]]; then\n    # Find workspace root (2 levels up from worktree)\n    WORKSPACE_ROOT=\"$(cd \"$(dirname \"$PWD\")/..\" \u0026\u0026 pwd)\"\n    \n    # Symlink layers if it doesn't exist\n    if [ ! -e \"layers\" ]; then\n        ln -s \"$WORKSPACE_ROOT/layers\" layers\n        echo \"✅ Symlinked layers/ to workspace worktree\"\n    fi\nfi\n```\n\n**Install**: `.git/hooks/post-checkout` (symlink to `.agent/hooks/post-checkout`)\n\n### Option 2: Document manual step\n\nUpdate `.agent/WORKTREE_GUIDE.md` with manual symlink step:\n```markdown\n## Creating Workspace Worktrees (Manual)\n\nIf you create worktrees manually with `git worktree add`:\n\n1. Create the worktree:\n   ```bash\n   git worktree add .workspace-worktrees/issue-N -b feature/branch\n   ```\n\n2. **Required**: Symlink layers directory:\n   ```bash\n   cd .workspace-worktrees/issue-N\n   ln -s ../../layers layers\n   ```\n\n3. Now you can work normally (build, test, etc.)\n```\n\n### Option 3: Deprecate workspace worktrees\n\nMake `.agent/scripts/worktree_create.sh` the only supported way to create worktrees. This script already handles symlinks correctly for layer worktrees.\n\n## Recommendation\n\n**Option 1** - Provides best UX and catches both manual and scripted worktree creation.\n\n## Implementation Tasks\n\n- [ ] Create `.agent/hooks/post-checkout` hook script\n- [ ] Make hook executable (`chmod +x`)\n- [ ] Install hook: `ln -s ../../.agent/hooks/post-checkout .git/hooks/post-checkout`\n- [ ] Test with manual worktree creation\n- [ ] Update `.agent/WORKTREE_GUIDE.md` to note auto-symlinking\n- [ ] Add to workspace setup documentation\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- ✅ Manually created workspace worktrees automatically get `layers/` symlink\n- ✅ Hook works for new worktree creation\n- ✅ Existing worktrees can manually run hook to fix\n- ✅ No impact on layer worktrees (already working)\n- ✅ Documented in WORKTREE_GUIDE.md\n\n## Testing\n\n```bash\n# Test 1: Create new workspace worktree\ngit worktree add .workspace-worktrees/test-123 -b test-branch\ncd .workspace-worktrees/test-123\nls layers/  # Should exist (symlink)\nmake sync   # Should work\n\n# Test 2: Verify layer worktrees unaffected\n.agent/scripts/worktree_create.sh --issue 999 --type layer --layer core\n# Should work as before\n```\n\n## Priority\n\n**Medium** - Improves developer experience and testing capability\n\n## Effort\n\n**Small** (1 hour)\n\n---\n**🤖 Authored-By**: `Copilot CLI Agent` (Claude Sonnet 4.5)","files":null}]}